      • createResumingRequest

        public static SSR createResumingRequest(long sprId)
        Creates a resuming request SSR. This event is send when resuming starts in RAPI. SPRs can prepare for active state but will still need the MOTION_RESUME_REQUEST to go in active state.
        Parameters:
        sprId - id of the SPR to which the compound belongs
        Returns:
        the generated SSR
        This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • createResumeRequest

        public static SSR createResumeRequest(long sprId)
        Creates a resumed info SSR. This event is send after the resuming is finished by RAPI. Sunrise then allows SPRs to go in active state.
        Parameters:
        sprId - id of the SPR to which the compound belongs
        Returns:
        the generated SSR
        This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.
